-- Banca Etruria shares jump after takeover offer by Pop Vicenza 
-- By Francesca Landini
-- Thu May 29, 2014 03:28AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, May 29 (Reuters) - Shares in Italy's Banca Etruria <PEL.MI> rose more than 20 percent on Thursday after mid-sized bank Banca Popolare di Vicenza [BPVIC.MI] said it was ready to launch a takeover bid on the smaller rival.

Banca Popolare di Vicenza said in a statement it would offer to buy shares in the small lender at a price of 1 euro per share, with a premium of 25.8 percent on Banca Etruria Tuesday's closing price. [nI6N0O100J]